### Pattern 8 — Scroll-Triggered Color World Shift
Each major section has its own HSL canvas tone.
As user scrolls between sections, the document background HSL-interpolates.
Not a hard switch — a continuous color field transition.
```js
const sections = [
  { hue: 220, sat: 12, light: 6 },   // obsidian
  { hue: 24,  sat: 15, light: 8 },   // warm dark
  { hue: 200, sat: 20, light: 7 },   // deep blue
]
ScrollTrigger.create({
  trigger: sectionEl,
  onUpdate: (self) => {
    const from = sections[i], to = sections[i + 1]
    const h = gsap.utils.interpolate(from.hue, to.hue, self.progress)
    const s = gsap.utils.interpolate(from.sat, to.sat, self.progress)
    const l = gsap.utils.interpolate(from.light, to.light, self.progress)
    document.documentElement.style.setProperty(
      '--color-canvas', `hsl(${h}, ${s}%, ${l}%)`
    )
  }
})
```

